{"cursor":"6726","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox album \n| Name = Faces Type = Double album Artist = Earth, Wind & Fire Cover = Earth\n| Wind & Fire - Faces.jpg Released = October 14, 1980 Recorded = September,\n| 1980, George Massenburg/ARC Studios, West Los Angeles Genre = R&B Length =\n| 60:34 Label = ARC/Columbia Records Producer = Maurice White Last album = [[I\n| Am (Earth, Wind & Fire album)|I Am]] (1979) This album =\n| 'Faces' (1980) Next album = [[Raise!]] (1981) Misc = {{Singles Name\n| = Faces Type = studio Single 1 = Let Me Talk Single 1 date = September 5,\n| 1980 Single 2 = You Single 2 date = November 14, 1980 Single 3 = Back on the\n| Road Single 3 date = 1980 Single 4 = And Love Goes On Single 4 date =\n| January 12, 1981\n }} }} {{Album ratings |rev1 = Allmusic |rev1score = [ Allmusic\n review] |rev2 = Warr.org |rev2score =\n [http://www.warr.org/ewf.html#Faces Warr.org review] }}\n\n'Faces' is the tenth studio album, a double-LP by R&B artists Earth, Wind &\nFire, released in 1980 on ARC/Columbia Records. The album reached number 2 and\nnumber 10 on the Billboard Black and Pop albums charts. [\nFaces - Charts on Allmusic.com]\n\nIt has been certified gold in the US by the RIAA. [http://www.riaa.com/gold-\nandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS&artist=Earth%20Wind&format=ALBUM&go=Se-\narch&perPage=50 RIAA Certification for Faces] In a 2007 interview when\nasked which EWF album is his favorite Earth, Wind & Fire leader Maurice White\nreplied \"Probably Faces because we were really in tune, playing together and it\ngave us the opportunity to explore new areas\".\n\nThe lead-off single was \"Let Me Talk\". The songs \"You\", and \"Sparkle\" followed\nas single releases. Unlike previous Earth, Wind and Fire albums, there was no\nU.S. tour in support of the album. This was also the last Earth Wind and Fire\nrecording with guitarist Al McKay, who left the group the next year.\n","linknr":238,"url":"Faces_(Earth,_Wind_&_Fir